Brazilian Stock Movers: Banrisul, Gol Linhas, JBS, Petrobras

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-05-30T20:47:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/brazilian-stock-movers-jbs-rises-petrobras-santander-fall.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m.  New York  time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 0.5 percent to 63,953.93.  Banco do Estado do Rio Grande do Sul SA (BRSR6 BS), the
Brazilian bank known as Banrisul, fell 2.5 percent to 17.11
reais.  Brazil ’s total loan default rate rose to 4.9 percent in
April, from 3.7 percent in March, the central bank said today.
Defaults on consumer loans increased for a third straight month,
reaching 6.1 percent, their highest level since August.  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA (GOLL4)  (GOLL4 BS), Brazil’s
biggest airline by market value, jumped 3.2 percent to 20.14
reais. Lan Airlines SA may seek a deal with Gol should its
planned acquisition of Brazilian rival  Tam SA (TAMM4)  fail, Santiago-
based newspaper  El Mercurio  reported, citing an interview with
Ignacio Cueto, the Chilean airline’s chief executive officer.  JBS SA (JBSS3)  (JBSS3 BS), the world’s biggest beef producer,
gained 2.4 percent to 5.55 reais. J&F Participacoes SA, the
holding company that indirectly controls JBS, agreed to pay 350
million reais to buy a producer of hygiene and cleaning products
from Brazil’s Bertin Group, according to a J&F press official
who asked not to be identified due to internal policy.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS), Brazil’s state-
controlled oil company, slipped 0.9 percent to 24.08 reais.
Crude dropped in New York, headed for its first monthly decline
since August, on speculation fuel demand may falter amid a
slowdown in the U.S. economic recovery and  Europe ’s continuing
debt crisis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
